<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Day 4: The Crew Login</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to engagement</a>
    <div class="brand brand-sm">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>Day 4 · The Crew Login</h1>
      <p class="desc">A contractor built Skyway's crew portal login in raw, unparameterized SQL. The query template is even printed in the page footer for "debugging." Walk in.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story-box">
      <strong>The story.</strong> Crew members log in here to check schedules and report fatigue. The login takes
      <code>username</code> + <code>password</code> and pastes them straight into a SQL query. You don't need to
      know any user's password. You need to make the query <em>always true</em>.
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🛩️ Skyway Crew Portal · v0.9-beta</span>
          <span>Login · Help</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Crew sign-in</h2>
          <form method="POST" action="/challenge/4/login" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;max-width:380px">
            <input name="username" placeholder="Username" required class="flag-input">
            <input name="password" type="text" placeholder="Password" required class="flag-input">
            <button class="submit-btn">Sign in</button>
          </form>
          <% if (result && result.message) { %>
            <div class="result-msg error" style="display:block; margin-top:14px;"><%= result.message %></div>
          <% } %>
          <% if (attemptedQuery) { %>
            <p style="margin-top:18px;color:#888;font-size:0.9em">Debug. Query just executed:</p>
            <pre class="code-block" style="font-size:0.9em"><%= attemptedQuery %></pre>
          <% } %>
          <p style="margin-top:24px;color:#888;font-size:0.85em">
            <em>Backend query template (printed here for "debug"):</em><br>
            <code>SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='{u}' AND password='{p}'</code>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Why this works</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Your input turns the query into:<br>
          <code style="font-size:0.85em">SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='' OR '1'='1' -- ' AND password='...'</code><br>
          The <code>--</code> comments out the password check. <code>'1'='1'</code> is always true. The query returns the first user. Usually the admin.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
